== Roasted Green Beans ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Toss @green beans{6%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp}, 
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

== Miso Chili Chicken ==

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over 
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #medium pan{} (use a #large nonstick pan{} 
for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked 
through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Return same pan to medium-high heat. Add @sweet Thai chili sauce{2%tbsp}, 
@Miso sauce concentrate{1}, @ponzu sauce{12%ml}, and 2 TBSP water (¼ cup for 4 servings). 
Bring to a simmer and cook until just thickened, ~{1%minute}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Season with 
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Lemongrass Rice ==

Massage @microwavable lemongrass rice{1%unit} in package to break up grains; partially 
open top. Insert @butter{1%tbsp} into package (for 4 servings, use 1 TBSP butter per 
package). Microwave for ~{90%seconds}.

Fluff with a #fork{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Divide rice between plates. Thinly slice chicken; place on top of rice. Pour sauce 
over chicken and serve with green beans on the side.